trans-unit.source: Class loaders that support concurrent loading of classes are known as parallel capable class loaders and are required to register themselves at their class initialization time by invoking the ClassLoader.registerAsParallelCapable method. Note that the ClassLoader class is registered as parallel capable by default. However, its subclasses still need to register themselves if they are parallel capable. In environments in which the delegation model is not strictly hierarchical, class loaders need to be parallel capable, otherwise class loading can lead to deadlocks because the loader lock is held for the duration of the class loading process (see loadClass methods).
trans-unit.target: 클래스의 동시로드를 지원하는 클래스 로더를 병렬 가능 클래스 로더라고하며 ClassLoader.registerAsParallelCapable 메서드 를 호출하여 클래스 초기화 시간에 자신을 등록해야합니다 . 점을 유의 ClassLoader 클래스가 기본적으로있는 병렬로 등록됩니다. 그러나 하위 클래스가 병렬 가능하다면 여전히 등록해야합니다. 위임 모델이 엄격하게 계층 적이 지 않은 환경에서 클래스 로더는 병렬이 가능해야합니다. 그렇지 않으면 클래스로드 프로세스 동안 로더 잠금이 유지되기 때문에 클래스로드로 인해 교착 상태가 발생할 수 있습니다 ( loadClass 메소드 참조 ).

trans-unit.source: Classes for generating and validating XML digital signatures. This package includes classes that represent the core elements defined in the W3C XML digital signature specification: XMLSignature, SignedInfo, CanonicalizationMethod, SignatureMethod, Reference, DigestMethod, XMLObject, Manifest, SignatureProperties, and SignatureProperty. KeyInfo types are defined in the javax.xml.crypto.dsig.keyinfo subpackage. XMLSignatureFactory is an abstract factory that creates XMLSignature objects from scratch or from a pre-existing XML representation, such as a DOM node. TransformService is a service provider interface for creating and plugging in implementations of transform and canonicalization algorithms.
trans-unit.target: XML 디지털 서명을 생성하고 유효성을 검사하기위한 클래스입니다. 이 패키지에는 W3C XML 디지털 서명 사양에 정의 된 핵심 요소 인 XMLSignature , SignedInfo , CanonicalizationMethod , SignatureMethod , Reference , DigestMethod , XMLObject , Manifest , SignatureProperties 및 SignatureProperty 를 나타내는 클래스가 포함되어 있습니다 . KeyInfo 유형은 javax.xml.crypto.dsig.keyinfo 서브 패키지에 정의되어 있습니다. XMLSignatureFactory 생성 추상 공장 XMLSignature 의를처음부터 또는 DOM 노드와 같은 기존 XML 표현의 개체. TransformService 는 변환 및 정규화 알고리즘의 구현을 만들고 플러그인하기위한 서비스 공급자 인터페이스입니다.

trans-unit.source: Classes for parsing and processing KeyInfo elements and structures. KeyInfo is an optional element that enables the recipient(s) to obtain the key needed to validate an XMLSignature. KeyInfo may contain keys, names, certificates and other public key management information, such as in-band key distribution or key agreement data. This package contains classes representing types defined in the W3C specification for XML Signatures, such as KeyName, KeyValue, RetrievalMethod, X509Data, X509IssuerSerial, and PGPData. KeyInfoFactory is an abstract factory that creates KeyInfo objects from scratch.
trans-unit.target: KeyInfo 요소 및 구조 를 구문 분석하고 처리하기위한 클래스입니다 . KeyInfo 는 수신자가 XMLSignature 의 유효성을 검사하는 데 필요한 키를 얻을 수 있도록하는 선택적 요소입니다 . KeyInfo 에는 키, 이름, 인증서 및 대역 내 키 배포 또는 키 계약 데이터와 같은 기타 공개 키 관리 정보가 포함될 수 있습니다. 이 패키지에는 KeyName , KeyValue , RetrievalMethod , X509Data , X509IssuerSerial 및 PGPData 와 같은 XML 서명에 대한 W3C 사양에 정의 된 유형을 나타내는 클래스가 포함되어 있습니다 . For SSLEngine objects, an application should call closeOutbound() and send any remaining messages to the peer. Likewise, an application should receive any remaining messages from the peer before calling closeInbound(). The underlying transport mechanism can then be closed after both sides of the SSLEngine have been closed. trans-unit.source: Code generators have three distinct ways to process a constant string operand S in a string concatenation expression. First, S can be materialized as a reference (using ldc) and passed as an ordinary argument (recipe '\1'). Or, S can be stored in the constant pool and passed as a constant (recipe '\2') . Finally, if S contains neither of the recipe tag characters ('\1', '\2') then S can be interpolated into the recipe itself, causing its characters to be inserted into the result.

trans-unit.source: Collection usage threshold is a manageable attribute only applicable to some garbage-collected memory pools. After a Java virtual machine has expended effort in reclaiming memory space by recycling unused objects in a memory pool at garbage collection time, some number of bytes in the memory pools that are garbaged collected will still be in use. The collection usage threshold allows a value to be set for this number of bytes such that if the threshold is exceeded, a collection usage threshold exceeded notification will be emitted by the MemoryMXBean. In addition, the collection usage threshold count will then be incremented.

trans-unit.source: Collections and streams, while bearing some superficial similarities, have different goals. Collections are primarily concerned with the efficient management of, and access to, their elements. By contrast, streams do not provide a means to directly access or manipulate their elements, and are instead concerned with declaratively describing their source and the computational operations which will be performed in aggregate on that source. However, if the provided stream operations do not offer the desired functionality, the BaseStream.iterator() and BaseStream.spliterator() operations can be used to perform a controlled traversal.
